'''Philip Ewing "Phil" Boyd''' (born [[June 5]], [[1876]] - died ?) was a [[Canada|Canadian]] [[Rowing (sport)|rower]] who competed in the [[1904 Summer Olympics]].

In 1904 he was a member of Canadian boat, which won the silver medal in the eights.

